## Executive Summary (≤150 words)
Our firm faces foreign exchange (FX) risk from a €20 million receivable due in one year. Because revenues will be received in euros but reported in U.S. dollars, fluctuations in the EUR/USD exchange rate could materially impact realized USD proceeds. Based on current market data, the EUR/USD spot rate is approximately 1.14–1.16 USD/EUR (), while the 1-year forward rate is 1.0935. This gap highlights expectations of potential euro depreciation. If the euro weakens over the next year, our USD proceeds will decline, creating earnings volatility. Hedging is therefore worth considering to stabilize cash flows and reduce financial uncertainty.
