## Background & Objectives
As outlined in Scenario 4, we are exposed to euro currency risk on a €20,000,000 receivable expected in one year. The core issue is transaction exposure: the USD value of this receivable will fluctuate with exchange rate movements. Recent market data shows the EUR/USD exchange rate trading around 1.147 (), with a 52-week range between approximately 1.07 and 1.20 (), demonstrating meaningful volatility. Our objective is to evaluate whether hedging can reduce uncertainty, protect firm value, and provide more predictable cash flows while still considering potential upside.
