## Methods
We are evaluating three primary hedge families:
1. Forward Contract
Locks in the forward rate of 1.0935 USD/EUR.
Pros: Eliminates uncertainty; simple and cost-effective.
Cons: No participation in favorable currency movements.
2. Money Market Hedge
Uses borrowing/lending in USD and EUR to replicate a forward position.
Pros: Flexible; grounded in interest rate parity.
Cons: Requires balance sheet capacity and depends on interest rates.
3. Options (EUR Put / USD Call)
Provides the right to sell euros at a fixed strike price.
Pros: Downside protection with upside potential.
Cons: Requires upfront premium (e.g., $0.019 per EUR), reducing net proceeds.
